The article discusses a meeting between the President of the United States and various business leaders and entrepreneurs to discuss the economic benefits of immigration reform. The participants in the meeting shared the belief that immigration reform would have positive economic effects, creating a fair playing field for employers and workers. The President emphasized that immigration reform would boost the country's economic recovery, citing a recent report from the Congressional Budget Office that supported this claim. The President also highlighted the negative impact of the broken immigration system on businesses, workers, and the economy. Some of the business owners present at the meeting were immigrants themselves, who came to the United States to build a better life and are now contributing to the economy by creating American jobs. The President expressed his support for bipartisan efforts in Congress and urged Congressional leaders to take action to strengthen the economy, improve the fiscal outlook, and create new opportunities for Americans.